<p class="p">We used the occurrence probability for each species provided by the species distribution models as described in the previous section. For each network, scenario, and time horizon (current, 2050, and 2080, respectively), the decrease in occurrence probability for species 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic> was given by 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="m1" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
     <msup class="msup">
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msup>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <msubsup class="msubsup">
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mn class="mn">0</mn>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msubsup>
     <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     <msubsup class="msubsup">
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mi class="mi">h</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msubsup>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">/</mo>
     <msubsup class="msubsup">
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mn class="mn">0</mn>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, where 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="m2" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msubsup class="msubsup">
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mn class="mn">0</mn>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the occurrence probability at present time and 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="m3" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msubsup class="msubsup">
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mi class="mi">h</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msubsup>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the occurrence probability at time horizon 
 <italic class="italic">h</italic>. For those species with an undetermined occurrence probability, the decrease in occurrence was assigned to the value of the maximum decrement of occurrence within its community for that particular time horizon and scenario.
</p>
